\subsection{Summation formula}


Read ``the summation of $x_i$ from $i=1$ to $n$"
\[\sum_{i=1}^n x_i\]%\pause
Repeat this 10 times ....%\pause
$$\sum_{i=1}^n x_i=x_1+x_2+\cdots +x_n$$%\pause
which means
$$\bar{x} = \frac{x_1+\cdots +x_n}{n}=\frac1n \sum_{i=1}^n x_i = \sum_{i=1}^n \frac{x_i }{n}$$


