\section{$z-$score and Outliers}



The \textbf{$z-$score} is computed using the mean and standard deviation as
$$
z=\frac{x-\bar{x}}{s}
$$
where $\bar{x}$ is the mean and $s$ is the standard deviation.%\pause

For our study data we had $\bar{x}=8.56$ and $s=8.34$.

